Fix readme files (#53)

* enabled lfs tracking for pdf and png

* conversion of targeted lfs files

* blind copy core docs to datastore since it covers most data there

* conversion of targeted lfs files

* updating docs for core

* cleanup image, textual flow, obsolete data

* turned dot list into html table

* fix adding static, and not correct, HOME information to man pages

* updating data lake readme and man page data

* updating diagrams

* Update README.md

image include naming fix

* consistency cleanup between modules, info cleanup for datastore (not done)

* generating new graphics

* typo fixes

* updates to main readme

* core redo to explain more

* more cleanup and slight re-org of the info to flow differently

* details for the datastore library

* spellcheck

* updated install (from source) guide

* updated fetcher docs, language standardization with datastore and datalake

* linked clw readme to top level

* updated playbook readme, not done yet

* slight cleanup and clarrification

* slight format change

* reworking clw readme

* 127 ip to localhost

* typo fixes

* updated playbook graphics

* playbook usage update and re-order/grouping

* fixed the playbook export readme

* spellcheck

* more descriptive verbiage

* added clarifying text to when routes are used

* more detail, spellcheck

* cleanup of images

* fix any char match to actual period

* simplified description of types of reports

* example corrections and small cleanups

* import-tshark more useful exampls

* playbook-nessus: fixed help and version output to fix man page

* nmdl-insert: typo, another example

* more examples, cleaning and clarifing text

* numerous verbiage and example updates to clarify useage

* fixed example

* fixed example

* standardizing, example cleanup, documenting functionality changes

* author block update, man page contains link to repo for images, remove refs to other programs

* last spell check of all README.md
